actions.comment:
To save your canvas drawing as a byte array, use `SKBitmap.Encode()` to get an `SKData` object and call `.ToArray()` on it.

Note: `SKBitmap.Decode(new byte[0])` returns `null` because there's no valid image data to decode. Create your bitmap with `new SKBitmap(width, height)` instead.

Here's a corrected example:

```csharp
int width = 100, height = 100;
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(width, height);
using var canvas = new SKCanvas(bitmap);
canvas.Clear(SKColors.Transparent);

using var path = new SKPath();
path.AddCircle(50, 50, 20);
using var paint = new SKPaint { Color = SKColors.Red, IsAntialias = true };
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);

// Encode as PNG and get bytes
using var data = bitmap.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
byte[] bytes = data.ToArray();
```

You can also encode directly to a `Stream`:

```csharp
bitmap.Encode(stream, SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
```
